The paper deals with statistical properties and risk analysis of kernel k-means, which is a popular clustering algorithm in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as clustering is a common task in these fields. The paper also involves computational approximations and statistical analysis, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.ST (Statistics).
